parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to lower to the ground, making it difficult to drive and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Vehicle Too Low" warning light comes on
the air suspension fault light comes on
the vehicle lowers to the ground
the vehicle scrapes on the ground
the ride is rough
the vehicle bounces or shakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the strut can cause the vehicle to lower to the ground, making it difficult to drive and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Vehicle Too Low" warning light comes on
the air suspension fault light comes on
the vehicle lowers to the ground
the vehicle scrapes on the ground
the ride is rough
the vehicle bounces or shakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air compressor can cause the air suspension system to malfunction, leading to the vehicle lowering to the ground and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Vehicle Too Low" warning light comes on
the air suspension fault light comes on
the vehicle lowers to the ground
the vehicle scrapes on the ground
the ride is rough
the vehicle bounces or shakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise from the prop shaft can be a sign of a more serious problem, such as a failing prop shaft, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Clicking noise from the prop shaft when driving over bumps or speed bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle hesitates to respond
the ABS warning light and traction control warning light are illuminated
the message "Park Brake Fault" is displayed
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the vehicle accelerates while applying the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Accelerator Pedal Interference
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake pedal and accelerator pedal can cause accidental simultaneous depression of both pedals, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal and accelerator pedal are too close together
causing the driver to depress both pedals at the same time when trying to stop the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake caliper freezes
causing the vehicle to pull to one side while braking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration when braking can cause the vehicle to surge forward, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly while braking
often with a loud roaring sound from the engine
and may continue to move forward even when the brake pedal is fully depressed. In some cases
the vehicle may only stop when shifted into park or turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also cause emotional distress and a loss of confidence in the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without warning. The accelerator pedal may stick or feel unresponsive
and the vehicle may lurch forward or speed up unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also cause emotional distress and a loss of confidence in the vehicle.
symptoms: The transmission may slip or hesitate
causing the vehicle to jerk or stumble. The transmission may also fail to engage or disengage
leading to loss of power or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also cause emotional distress and a loss of confidence in the vehicle.
symptoms: The clutch may fail to engage or disengage
causing the vehicle to jerk or stumble. The clutch may also make a loud grinding or screeching noise
indicating failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause a fire hazard, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also cause emotional distress and a loss of confidence in the vehicle.
symptoms: Oil may leak from the engine or transmission
causing a puddle or stain under the vehicle. The vehicle may also have a burning smell or smoke
indicating a fire hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS and brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose control or crash, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also cause emotional distress and a loss of confidence in the vehicle.
symptoms: The ABS light may illuminate on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the anti-lock braking system. The brakes may also feel spongy or unresponsive
or the vehicle may pull to one side when braking.
